Heat panini or George Forman grill to medium heat. Split hoagie buns in half. Spread yellow mustard on bottom halves, if you like. Top with pork, ham, cheese and pickles. Cover with top halves of buns; cut in half to make 4 sandwiches. Butter outsides of sandwiches. Place sandwiches on heated grill. Cook about 8 to 10 minutes or until sandwich is hot and buns are toasted.